<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	19.
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Counterparts
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;This Agreement may be executed in any number of counterparts, each of which when so executed and delivered shall be taken to be an original; but such counterparts shall together constitute one and the same document.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	20.
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Successor to Company
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company shall require any successor (whether direct or indirect, by purchase, merger, consolidation or otherwise) to all or substantially all of the business or assets of the Company expressly to assume and agree to perform this Agreement to the same extent that the Company would be required to perform it if no succession had taken place.&nbsp;&nbsp;Failure of the Company to obtain an assumption of this Agreement at or prior to the effectiveness of any succession shall be a material breach of this Agreement.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	21.
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Gender Neutral
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Wherever used herein, a pronoun in the masculine gender shall be considered as including the feminine gender unless the context clearly indicates otherwise.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	IN WITNESS WHEREOF, the parties have executed this Agreement effective on the date and year first above written.

<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:36PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:50%;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">

<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	RELEASE

<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	I enter into this Separation Agreement and Release (the &#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Release
</FONT>
	&#8221;) pursuant to Section 4(b) or 5(a), as applicable, of the Amended and Restated Employment Agreement between aTyr Pharma, Inc., a Delaware corporation (the &#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Employer
</FONT>
	&#8221;) and me dated December ___, 2015 (the &#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Employment Agreement
</FONT>
	&#8221;).&nbsp;&nbsp;I acknowledge that my timely execution and return and my non-revocation of this Release are conditions to the payments and benefits pursuant to Section 4(b) or 5(a), as applicable, of the Employment Agreement.&nbsp;&nbsp;I therefore agree to the following terms:
</P>
<P STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	1.
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:72PT;">

</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;I voluntarily release and forever discharge the Employer, its affiliated and related entities, its and their respective predecessors, successors and assigns, its and their respective employee benefit plans and fiduciaries of such plans, and the current and former officers, directors, shareholders, members, employees, attorneys, accountants and agents of each of the foregoing in their official and personal capacities (collectively referred to as the &#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Releasees
</FONT>
	&#8221;) generally from all claims, demands, debts, damages and liabilities of every name and nature, known or unknown (&#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Claims
</FONT>
	&#8221;) that, as of the date when I sign this Release, I have, ever had, now claim to have or ever claimed to have had against any or all of the Releasees.&nbsp;&nbsp;This release includes, without limitation, all Claims:
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">

<A NAME="LIFE-EX103_474_HTM_OLE_LINK29">

<A NAME="LIFE-EX103_474_HTM_OLE_LINK30">
</A>
	I agree that the release set forth in this section shall be and remain in effect in all respects as a complete general release as to the matters released.&nbsp;&nbsp;This release does not extend to any obligations incurred under this Employment Agreement, under any ongoing Company benefit plans or for indemnification under any indemnification agreement, the Company&#8217;s Bylaws or applicable law.&nbsp;&nbsp;
<A NAME="LIFE-EX103_474_HTM_OLE_LINK7">
</A>
<A NAME="LIFE-EX103_474_HTM_OLE_LINK8">
</A>
	This release does not release claims that cannot be released as a matter of law,
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:8PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	ACTIVE/84027084.7
</FONT>
</P>

<A NAME="eolPage129"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="LIFE-EX103_474_HTM_OLE_LINK76">
</A>
<A NAME="LIFE-EX103_474_HTM_OLE_LINK77">
</A>
	including, but not limited to, my right to file a charge with or participate in a charge by the Equal Employment Opportunity Commission
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	, or any other local, state, or federal administrative body or government agency that is authorized to enforce or administer laws related to employment
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	, against the Company (with the understanding that any such filing or participation does not give me the right to recover any monetary damages against the Company; my release of claims herein bars me from recovering such monetary relief from the Company).
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	I agree that I shall not seek or accept damages of any nature, other equitable or legal remedies for my own benefit, attorney&#8217;s fees, or costs from any of the Releasees with respect to any Claim released by this Agreement.&nbsp;&nbsp;I represent that I have not assigned to any third party and I have not filed with any agency or court any Claim released by this Agreement.
</P>
<P STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	2.
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:72PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Ongoing Obligations
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;I reaffirm my ongoing obligations under the Employment Agreement, including without limitation my obligations under Section&#160;7 (&#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Confidential Information and Noncompetition
</FONT>
	&#8221;) and under Section 7 of the Prior Agreement (as defined in the Employment Agreement).
</P>
<P STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	3.
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:72PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	No Assignment
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;I represent that I have not assigned to any other person or entity any Claims against any Releasee.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	4.
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:72PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Right to Consider and Revoke Release
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;I acknowledge that I have been given the opportunity to consider this Release for a period of twenty-one (21) days from the date when it is tendered to me.&nbsp;&nbsp;In the event that I executed this Release within less than twenty-one (21) days, I acknowledge that such decision was entirely voluntary and that I had the opportunity to consider this Release until the end of the twenty-one&#160;(21) day period.&nbsp;&nbsp;To accept this Release, I shall deliver a signed Release to the Employer&#8217;s Vice President of Operations within such twenty-one&#160;(21) day period;
<FONT STYLE="FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	provided
</FONT>
	that I acknowledge that the Employer may change the designated recipient by notice.&nbsp;&nbsp;For a period of seven&#160;(7) days from the date when I execute this Release (the &#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Revocation&#160;Period
</FONT>
	&#8221;), I shall retain the right to revoke this Release by written notice that is received by the Employer&#8217;s Vice President of Operations or other Employer-designated recipient on or before the last day of the Revocation Period.&nbsp;&nbsp;This Release shall take effect only if it is executed within the twenty-one&#160;(21) day period as set forth above and if it is not revoked pursuant to the preceding sentence.&nbsp;&nbsp;If those conditions are satisfied, this Release shall become effective and enforceable on the date immediately following the last day of the Revocation Period (the &#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Effective Date
</FONT>
	&#8221;).
</P>
<P STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="LIFE-EX103_474_HTM_OLE_LINK3">
</A>
<A NAME="LIFE-EX103_474_HTM_OLE_LINK4">
</A>
	5.
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:72PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	California Civil Code Section 1542
</FONT>
<A NAME="LIFE-EX103_474_HTM_OLE_LINK3">
</A>
<A NAME="LIFE-EX103_474_HTM_OLE_LINK4">
</A>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;I acknowledge that I have been advised to consult with legal counsel and am familiar with the provisions of California Civil Code Section&#160;1542, a statute that otherwise prohibits the release of unknown claims, which provides as follows:
</P>
<P STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:15.38%;MARGIN-RIGHT:15.38%;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="LIFE-EX103_474_HTM_OLE_LINK33">
</A>
<A NAME="LIFE-EX103_474_HTM_OLE_LINK34">
</A>
	A GENERAL RELEASE DOES NOT EXTEND TO CLAIMS WHICH THE CREDITOR DOES NOT KNOW OR SUSPECT TO EXIST IN HIS OR HER FAVOR AT THE TIME OF EXECUTING THE RELEASE, WHICH IF KNOWN BY HIM OR HER MUST HAVE MATERIALLY AFFECTED HIS OR HER SETTLEMENT WITH THE DEBTOR.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	14
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:8PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">

	I, being aware of said code section, agree to expressly waive any rights
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	I
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	may have thereunder, as well as under any other statute or common law principles of similar effect.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	6.
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:72PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Other Terms
</FONT>
	.
</P>
<P STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:15.38%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(a)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:72PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Legal Representation; Review of Release
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;I acknowledge that I have been advised to discuss all aspects of this Release with my attorney, that I have carefully read and fully understand all of the provisions of this Release and that I am voluntarily entering into this Release.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:15.38%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(b)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:72PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Binding Nature of Release
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;This Release shall be binding upon me and upon my heirs, administrators, representatives and executors.
</P>
<P STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:15.38%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(c)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:72PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Amendment
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;This Release may be amended only upon a written agreement executed by the Employer and me.
</P>
<P STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:15.38%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(d)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:72PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Severability
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;In the event that at any future time it is determined by an arbitrator or court of competent jurisdiction that any covenant, clause, provision or term of this Release is illegal, invalid or unenforceable, the remaining provisions and terms of this Release shall not be affected thereby and the illegal, invalid or unenforceable term or provision shall be severed from the remainder of this Release.&nbsp;&nbsp;In the event of such severance, the remaining covenants shall be binding and enforceable.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:15.38%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(e)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:72PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Governing Law and Interpretation
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;This Release shall be deemed to be made and entered into in the State of California, and shall in all respects be interpreted, enforced and governed under the laws of the State of California, without giving effect to the conflict of laws principles of such State.&nbsp;&nbsp;The language of all parts of this Release shall in all cases be construed as a whole, according to its fair meaning, and not strictly for or against either the Employer or me.
</P>
<P STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:15.38%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(f)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:72PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Entire Agreement; Absence of Reliance
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;I acknowledge that I am not relying on any promises or representations by the Employer or any of its agents, representatives or attorneys regarding any subject matter addressed in this Release.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	So agreed.
</P>

	Exhibit 10.16
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	ATYR PHARMA,
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-TRANSFORM:UPPERCASE;">
	Inc.

<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;TEXT-TRANSFORM:UPPERCASE;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	EXECUTIVE SEVERANCE AND CHANGE IN CONTROL POLICY
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;TEXT-TRANSFORM:UPPERCASE;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Adopted on December 21, 2015
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;">
	The purpose of this Executive Severance and Change in Control Policy (the &#8220;Policy&#8221;) of aTyr Pharma, Inc. (the &#8220;Company&#8221;) is to provide certain senior management employees of the Company with certain compensation and benefits in the event of a termination of employment without Cause (as defined below) or for Good Reason (as defined below), under the terms and conditions described in this Policy.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<DIV ALIGN="LEFT">
<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; WIDTH:100%;">
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="WIDTH:3.85%;WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;

<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="WIDTH:3.85%;WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">

<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">

</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Termination Not in Connection with a Sale Event
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:3.85%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	If the employment of an Eligible Employee (as defined below) is terminated by the Company without Cause (as defined below) or the Eligible Employee resigns for Good Reason (as defined below), then subject to such Eligible Employee&#8217;s execution and non-revocation of a severance agreement within 60 days following the date of such termination, including a general release of claims acceptable to the Company, such Eligible Employee shall be entitled to receive the following benefits:
</P>

	&nbsp;

<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	Acceleration of the time-based vesting provisions of outstanding stock options and other equity awards in which the employee would have vested if he or she had remained employed for an additional 12 months following the date of termination; provided, however, that for avoidance of doubt, for any equity award that includes both a performance-based vesting condition (which would include the achievement of a certain stock price) and a time-based vesting provision, no acceleration shall be provided unless such performance-based vesting condition has been satisfied as of the date of termination; and

	&#8220;Cause&#8221; shall mean (i) the employee&#8217;s dishonest statements or acts with respect to the Company or any affiliate of the Company, or any current or prospective customers, suppliers, vendors or other third parties with which such entity does business; (ii) the employee&#8217;s commission of (A) a felony or (B) any misdemeanor involving moral turpitude, deceit, dishonesty or fraud; (iii) the employee&#8217;s failure to perform his or her assigned duties and responsibilities to the reasonable satisfaction of the Company which failure continues, in the reasonable judgment of the Company, after written notice given to the employee by the Company; (iv) the employee&#8217;s gross negligence, willful misconduct or insubordination with respect to the Company or any affiliate of the Company; or (v) the employee&#8217;s material violation of any provision of any agreement(s) between the employee and the Company relating to noncompetition, nonsolicitation, nondisclosure and/or assignment of inventions.

<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&#8220;Good Reason&#8221; shall mean
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#000000;">
	(i) a material diminution in the employee&#8217;s responsibilities, authority or duties; (ii) a material diminution in the employee&#8217;s base compensation except for across-the-board compensation reductions similarly affecting all or substantially all similarly situated service providers of the Company; or (iii) a change of more than fifty (50) miles in the geographic location at which the employee provides services to the Company, in each case so long as the employee provides at least ninety (90) days&#8217; notice to the Company following the initial occurrence of any such event, the Company fails to cure such event within thirty (30) days thereafter and the employee terminates his or her employment within thirty (30) days after the end of such cure period.

	The amounts payable pursuant to this Policy shall be paid or commence to be paid within 60 days following the date of termination of employment, provided that if the 60-day period begins in one calendar year and ends in a second calendar year, such payments shall be paid or commence to be paid in the second calendar year by the last day of such 60-day period.

	In addition, upon the consummation of a Sale Event, to the extent Section 280G of the Internal Revenue Code is applicable to such employee, each employee shall be entitled to receive either: (a)&#160;payment of the full amounts set forth above to which the employee is entitled or (b)&#160;payment of such lesser amount that does not trigger excise taxes under Section 280G, whichever results in the employee receiving a higher amount after taking into account all federal, state, and local income, excise and employment taxes.

<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Base Salary Rate

<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">

<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	$

	9,292.00 per pay period (which equals $223,000.00 per year)

	In the event of any dispute or claim relating to or arising out of your employment relationship with the Company, this agreement, or the termination of your employment with the Company for any reason (including, but not limited to, any claims of breach of contract, defamation, wrongful termination or age, sex, sexual orientation, race, color, national origin, ancestry, marital status, religious creed, physical or mental disability or medical condition or other discrimination, retaliation or harassment), you and the Company agree that all such disputes shall be fully resolved by confidential, binding arbitration conducted by a single arbitrator through the American Arbitration Association (&#8220;AAA&#8221;) under the AAA&#8217;s National Rules for the Resolution of Employment Disputes then in effect, which are available online at the AAA&#8217;s website at www.adr.org.&nbsp;&nbsp;The arbitrator shall permit adequate discovery and is empowered to award all remedies otherwise available in a court of competent jurisdiction and any judgment rendered by the arbitrator may be entered by any court of competent jurisdiction.&nbsp;&nbsp;By executing this letter, you and the Company are both waiving the right to a jury trial with respect to any such disputes.&nbsp;&nbsp;Company shall bear the costs of the arbitrator, forum and filing fees.&nbsp;&nbsp;Each party shall bear its own respective attorney fees and all other costs, unless otherwise provided by law and awarded by the arbitrator.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	It is aTyr&#8217;s policy to respect fully the rights of your previous employers in their proprietary or confidential information.&nbsp;&nbsp;No employee is expected to disclose, or is allowed to use for aTyr&#8217;s purposes, any confidential or proprietary information he or she may have acquired as a result of previous employment.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	I am pleased to extend this offer to you and look forward to your acceptance.&nbsp;&nbsp;Please sign and return the enclosed copy of this offer letter as soon as possible to indicate your agreement with the terms of this offer.&nbsp;&nbsp;This offer will lapse if not signed and returned by May 2, 2011&nbsp;&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Once signed by you, this letter will constitute the complete agreement between you and aTyr Pharma, Inc. regarding employment matters and will supersede all prior written or oral agreements or understandings on these matters.
</P>

<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	It is aTyr&#8217;s policy to respect fully the rights of your previous employers in their proprietary or confidential information.&nbsp;&nbsp;No employee is expected to disclose, or is allowed to use for aTyr&#8217;s purposes, any confidential or proprietary information he or she may have acquired as a result of previous employment.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

	I am pleased to extend this offer to you and look forward to your acceptance.&nbsp;&nbsp;Please sign and return the enclosed copy of this offer letter as soon as possible to indicate your agreement with the terms of this offer.&nbsp;&nbsp;This offer will lapse if not signed and returned by Thursday, April 25, 2013.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</P>

	Once signed by you, this letter will constitute the complete agreement between you and aTyr Pharma, Inc. regarding employment matters and will supersede all prior written or oral agreements or understandings on these matter.

<EFX_CERTIFICATION>
<A NAME="FIS_CERTIFICATION_2"></A>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	CERTIFICATION OF PRINCIPAL EXECUTIVE OFFICER
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	PURSUANT TO
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#000000;">
	RULE 13a-14(a) AND 15d-14(a) OF THE SECURITIES EXCHANGE ACT
</FONT>
	,
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	AS ADOPTED PURSUANT TO SECTION 302
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	OF THE SARBANES-OXLEY ACT OF 2002
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	I, John D. Mendlein, certify that:
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	1. I have reviewed this Annual Report on Form 10-K of aTyr Pharma, Inc.;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	2. Based on my knowledge, this report does not contain any untrue statement of a material fact or omit to state a material fact necessary to make the statements made, in light of the circumstances under which such statements were made, not misleading with respect to the period covered by this report;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	3. Based on my knowledge, the consolidated financial statements, and other financial information included in this report, fairly present in all material respects the financial condition, results of operations and cash flows of the registrant as of, and for, the periods presented in this report;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	4. The registrant&#8217;s other certifying officer(s) and I are responsible for establishing and maintaining disclosure controls and procedures (as defined in Exchange Act Rules 13a-15(e) and 15d-15(e)) for the registrant and have:
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:4.54%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	a) Designed such disclosure controls and procedures, or caused such disclosure controls and procedures to be designed under our supervision, to ensure that material information relating to the registrant, including its consolidated subsidiaries, is made known to us by others within those entities, particularly during the period in which this report is being prepared;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:4.54%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	b) Evaluated the effectiveness of the registrant&#8217;s disclosure controls and procedures and presented in this report our conclusions about the effectiveness of the disclosure controls and procedures, as of the end of the period covered by this report based on such evaluation; and
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:4.54%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	c) Disclosed in this report any change in the registrant&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting that occurred during the registrant&#8217;s most recent fiscal quarter (the registrant&#8217;s fourth fiscal quarter in the case of an annual report) that has materially affected, or is reasonably likely to materially affect, the registrant&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting; and
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	5. The registrant&#8217;s other certifying officer(s) and I have disclosed, based on our most recent evaluation of internal control over financial reporting, to the registrant&#8217;s auditors and the audit committee of the registrant&#8217;s board of directors (or persons performing the equivalent functions):
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:4.54%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	a) All significant deficiencies and material weaknesses in the design or operation of internal control over financial reporting which are reasonably likely to adversely affect the registrant&#8217;s ability to record, process, summarize and report financial information; and
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:4.54%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	b) Any fraud, whether or not material, that involves management or other employees who have a significant role in the registrant&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#160;
</P>

<EFX_EXHIBIT_31>
<A NAME="FIS_EXHIBIT_31_2"></A>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Exhibit 31.2
</P>
<EFX_CERTIFICATION>
<A NAME="FIS_CERTIFICATION_3"></A>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	CERTIFICATION OF THE PRINCIPAL FINANCIAL OFFICER
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	PURSUANT TO
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#000000;">
	RULE 13a-14(a) AND 15d-14(a) OF THE SECURITIES EXCHANGE ACT
</FONT>
	,
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	AS ADOPTED PURSUANT TO SECTION 302
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	OF THE SARBANES-OXLEY ACT OF 2002
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	I, John T. Blake, certify that:
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	1. I have reviewed this Annual Report on Form 10-K of aTyr Pharma, Inc.;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	2. Based on my knowledge, this report does not contain any untrue statement of a material fact or omit to state a material fact necessary to make the statements made, in light of the circumstances under which such statements were made, not misleading with respect to the period covered by this report;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	3. Based on my knowledge, the consolidated financial statements, and other financial information included in this report, fairly present in all material respects the financial condition, results of operations and cash flows of the registrant as of, and for, the periods presented in this report;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	4. The registrant&#8217;s other certifying officer(s) and I are responsible for establishing and maintaining disclosure controls and procedures (as defined in Exchange Act Rules 13a-15(e) and 15d-15(e)) for the registrant and have:
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:4.54%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	a) Designed such disclosure controls and procedures, or caused such disclosure controls and procedures to be designed under our supervision, to ensure that material information relating to the registrant, including its consolidated subsidiaries, is made known to us by others within those entities, particularly during the period in which this report is being prepared;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:4.54%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	b) Evaluated the effectiveness of the registrant&#8217;s disclosure controls and procedures and presented in this report our conclusions about the effectiveness of the disclosure controls and procedures, as of the end of the period covered by this report based on such evaluation; and
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:4.54%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	c) Disclosed in this report any change in the registrant&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting that occurred during the registrant&#8217;s most recent fiscal quarter (the registrant&#8217;s fourth fiscal quarter in the case of an annual report) that has materially affected, or is reasonably likely to materially affect, the registrant&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting; and
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:4.54%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	5. The registrant&#8217;s other certifying officer(s) and I have disclosed, based on our most recent evaluation of internal control over financial reporting, to the registrant&#8217;s auditors and the audit committee of the registrant&#8217;s board of directors (or persons performing the equivalent functions):
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:4.54%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	a) All significant deficiencies and material weaknesses in the design or operation of internal control over financial reporting which are reasonably likely to adversely affect the registrant&#8217;s ability to record, process, summarize and report financial information; and
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:4.54%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	b) Any fraud, whether or not material, that involves management or other employees who have a significant role in the registrant&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#160;
</P>

	AS ADOPTED PURSUANT TO
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:4.54%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	In connection with the Annual Report on Form 10-K of aTyr Pharma, Inc. (the &#8220;Company&#8221;) for the period ended December&#160;31, 2015, as filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission on the date hereof (the &#8220;Report&#8221;), I, John D. Mendlein, Chief Executive Officer of the Company, certify, pursuant to 18 U.S.C. Section&#160;1350, as adopted pursuant to Section&#160;906 of the Sarbanes-Oxley Act of 2002, that to my knowledge:
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:4.54%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	1. The Report fully complies with the requirements of Section&#160;13(a) or 15(d) of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934; and
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:4.54%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	2. The information contained in the Report fairly presents, in all material respects, the financial condition and results of operations of the Company.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#160;

<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">

<EFX_CERTIFICATION>
<A NAME="FIS_CERTIFICATION_5"></A>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	CERTIFICATION
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#000000;">
	PURSUANT TO 18 U.S.C. SECTION 1350,
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	AS ADOPTED PURSUANT TO
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	SECTION 906 OF THE SARBANES-OXLEY ACT OF 2002
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#000000;">
	)
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:4.54%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	In connection with the Annual Report on Form 10-K of aTyr Pharma, Inc. (the &#8220;Company&#8221;) for the period ended December&#160;31, 2015, as filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission on the date hereof (the &#8220;Report&#8221;), I, John T. Blake, Principal Financial and Accounting Officer of the Company, certify, pursuant to 18 U.S.C. Section&#160;1350, as adopted pursuant to Section&#160;906 of the Sarbanes-Oxley Act of 2002, that to my knowledge:
</P>
